item.title: CVE-2022-2488|2024-08-03T00:39:07.861Z -- wavlink -- wn535k2
item.description: A vulnerability was found in WAVLINK WN535K2 and WN535K3 and classified as critical. This issue affects some unknown processing of the file /cgi-bin/touchlist_sync.cgi. The manipulation of the argument IP leads to os command injection. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.
